{"serial": "51018", "department_serial": 49, "code": "EE3046", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Microcomputer Theory and Laboratory", "ch": "微算機原理與實作"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Tsai, Jang-Zern"], "ch": ["蔡章仁"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 1, "session": ["A", "B", "C"]}, "loc": {"building": "E1", "room": "223"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "電機工程學系", "en": "Department of Electrical Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "部分英語", "en": "Partially English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 6, "selected": 50, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "課程目標：經由教師課堂講解及學生動手實習，讓學生建立在個人電腦的架構、運作、設計等方面的知識和能力，做為將來學習相關課程的基礎。\n課程概述：微算機原理是電機系的特色課程之一，雖無艱深的理論，但必須踏實的動手和動腦才能真正學好。經由對微處理機硬體架構的剖析和運作細節的分解，學生將對電腦強大功能的原理恍然大悟。透過對組合語言的設計撰寫和執行驗證，學生將習得在更深入的層次操控電腦使其發揮更大的功能。學生具備本課程所建立的基礎，再經過本系相關課程的洗禮，將從單純的電腦使用者蛻變成設計者，參與電腦及其他尖端科技的創新與進化。本課程並注重學生專業倫理的涵養。", "en": "\"Through lecturing of the teacher and hand-on practice and design of the students, the students will acquire profound knowledge and skills in the architecture, operation, and design of personal computers, which lays the ground for future study on related courses.\""}, "outline": {"ch": "1. 導論\n- 課程概述\n- 專業倫理\n2. 微處理機硬體\n- 硬體架構\n- 運作原理\n- 輸出入界面\n- 記憶體界面\n- 匯流排界面\n- 插斷界面\n3. 組合語言\n- 指令集\n- 機器碼\n- 定址模式\n- 程式結構\n- 程式撰寫及偵錯工具\n4. 實作\n- 學習微算機訓練器\n- 設計及撰寫組合語言程式\n- 在訓練器上驗證組合語言程式", "en": "1. Introduction\n- Overview of the course\n- Ethics for Microprocessor Engineers\n2. Microprocessor hardware\n- Hardware architecture\n- Operation principle\n- Input and output interface\n- Memory interface\n- Bus interface\n- Interrupt interface\n3. Assembly languages\n- Instruction set\n- Machine code\n- Addressing modes\n- Program structure\n- Programming and debugging tools\n4. Laboratory\n- Practice the microprocessor trainer\n- Design of assembly programs\n- Verification of assembly progra